This paper deals with the topic of moving target defense, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the automatic synthesis of program variants, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper involves source code transformations, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also deals with the concept of computation diversity, which is related to system design and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the synthesis of large sets of program variants, which could potentially involve distributed computing (cs.DC).
